Package chessapi4j

Class Game

java.lang.Object
chessapi4j.Game
All Implemented Interfaces:
Iterable<Position>
public class Game extends Object implements Iterable<Position>
The Game class represents a chess game. The class Provides a structured representation of a chess game and has methods to access, modify, and represent the game in PGN format.
Since:
1.1.0
Author:
lunalobos

    • addMove

      public Position addMove(String move) throws MovementException
      Adds a move to the game. The move is expected to be in UCI Notation. The move is executed in the current position of the game and the new position is added to the list of positions of the game. The last position of the game is returned.
      Parameters:
      move - the move in UCI/SAN format
      Returns:
      the last position of the game
      Throws:
      MovementException - if the move is illegal
      Since:
      1.2.5
